<@U3M4RRNQ5> <@U0261PCRQ> <@U051P3FPY> for our dx enrollment meeting today,  please download the launchbox data that i dropped in the compass ux channel. if you need some extra reading feel free to peruse the entire thing :wink: but here are the relevant pages and data that i'll be going over in our kick off:

*Page 2*
- Discovery use was minimal in the first couple weeks of testing. Why? Because it wasn’t clear from onboarding what it was, and enrollment was a barrier to content.

*Page 40*
- Barriers to trying or using a discovery are:
-- TIME: Trying a discovery takes more time than some have
-- INTEREST: Some topics just don’t interest them; and some content within a topic is unappealing (especially food)
- They don’t like having to download them before getting a sense for what they are
- Instead, they want immediate access to the discovery through clear descriptions, more info, and short streaming videos (sample) prior to sign-up
- For some, confusion included:
-- Unclear about the concept during setup
-- Overtime, it never become clear
-- The process was not as clear as it could be:
-- Didn’t understand that you need to ‘enroll’
-- Unclear about ‘next steps’ in the process in general
-- Unclear what would happen at the end of a discovery (“will it just go away?”)

*Page 66*
- Remove barriers (time & interest) to experiencing discoveries, for example:
-- Explain the discovery on the surface in clear, concrete terms
-- Provide 10-30 second experience (streaming) prior to downloading or enrolling
-- Offer downloading and enrollment after they have committed interest
